Date: Mon, 22 Nov 1999 00:40:24 -0200
From: Claudio Maierovitch Pessanha Henriques <claudiomph@uol.com.br>

We hear (and read!) about the risk of blood transmission of visceral
leishmaniais. Would anyone have information about control measures for
preventing transmission from blood in endemic areas?
--
Claudio Maierovitch Pessanha Henriques, MD, MPH
Agencia Nacional de Vigilancia Sanitaria
Ministerio da Saude, Brasil
e-mail: claudio.henriques@saude.gov.br
[According to Benenson's Control of Communicable Diseases Manual, normal
blood & body fluid precautions, which should in any case be taken because
of the risks of hepatitis & HIV, are adequate. Please reply direct to
Claudio at <claudio.henriques@saude.gov.br>. - Mod.JW
